HCP Terraform teams and permissions

Access control hierarchy : 
Users : Can belong to multiple teams
Teams : Granted persmission at the org, project and workspace levels.
Permissions : Additive model : the highest permission always wins. Follow the principle of least privileges.

Team visibility : Visible and Secret
Team tokens : has the same level of access to the workspace as the team.

Organisational level : Broad permissions like manage all workspaces, manage policies, manage vcs settings, view all workspaces.
project level : Permissions scoped to a project and all workspaces within it ( Read, write, maintain and custom )
Workspace level : Permissions on a specific workspace such as admin , read, write, plan or custom.

PRIVATE REGISTRY : 
-----------------
using private modules using src address : app.terraform.io/<organisation-name>/terraform/<name>/<provider>
module "webapp" {
  source = app.terraform.io/////
  name = var.name
  prefix = var.prefix
  version = "1.0.0"
}

KEY TAKEAWAYS : 
  -  The private registry lets you share modules/providers privately within the org.
  -  u can also curate approved modules/providers alongside ur private ones.
  -  private modules are published from VCS repos and versioned with git TAGS .
  -  The source format includes Hostname : app.terraform.io/<organisation-name>/terraform/<name>/<provider>
